<Base title={title} description={description} activeSection="company">
<style>
.nav-item>a:hover,.nav-item.active>a{color:#fff;}
  .nav-item.has-drop>a::after{content:' ▾';font-size:0.65rem;}
  
  
  .nav-dropdown a:hover{color:#fff;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.06);padding-left:24px;}
  
  .nav-cta:hover{background:var(--orange-bright)!important;}

.page-hero h1{font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:clamp(2.8rem,6vw,4.5rem);color:#fff;margin-bottom:20px;line-height:1;}
  .page-hero p{font-size:1.1rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.6);max-width:600px;margin:0 auto;line-height:1.7;}

  /* MISSION */
  .mission-section{padding:88px 56px;max-width:920px;margin:0 auto;display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:72px;align-items:center;}
  .mission-text 
  .mission-text h2{font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:2.6rem;line-height:1.05;margin-bottom:24px;}
  .mission-text p{color:var(--ink-mid);line-height:1.8;font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:16px;}
  .mission-visual{background:var(--navy-deep);border-radius:16px;padding:40px;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:20px;}
  .stat-row{display:flex;gap:32px;}
  .stat-item{flex:1;}
  .stat-num{font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:2.8rem;color:var(--orange);line-height:1;}
  .stat-label{font-size:0.78rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.45);letter-spacing:0.06em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-top:4px;}
  .stat-divider{height:1px;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.08);}

  /* VALUES */
  .values-section{background:var(--bg-warm);padding:80px 56px;}
  .values-section .section-head{text-align:center;margin-bottom:56px;}
  .values-section h2{font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:2.4rem;margin-top:8px;}
  .values-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:32px;max-width:1100px;margin:0 auto;}
  .value-card{background:#fff;border-radius:10px;padding:32px;border:1px solid var(--rule);}
  .value-ico{font-size:2rem;margin-bottom:16px;}
  .value-card h3{font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:800;font-size:1.2rem;margin-bottom:8px;letter-spacing:0.04em;}
  .value-card p{font-size:0.88rem;color:var(--ink-mid);line-height:1.7;}

  /* STORY */
  .story-section{padding:88px 56px;max-width:760px;margin:0 auto;}
  .story-section 
  .story-section h2{font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:2.4rem;margin-bottom:32px;}
  .story-section p{color:var(--ink-mid);line-height:1.85;font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:20px;}
  blockquote{border-left:4px solid var(--orange);padding:16px 24px;background:var(--orange-pale);border-radius:0 8px 8px 0;margin:32px 0;font-style:italic;font-size:1.05rem;color:var(--ink);line-height:1.7;}

  /* TEAM */
  .team-section{background:var(--bg-warm);padding:80px 56px;}
  .team-section .section-head{text-align:center;margin-bottom:56px;}
  .team-section h2{font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:2.4rem;margin-top:8px;}
  .team-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);gap:24px;max-width:1100px;margin:0 auto;}
  .team-card{background:#fff;border-radius:10px;overflow:hidden;border:1px solid var(--rule);text-align:center;}
  .team-avatar{height:120px;background:var(--navy);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-size:2.5rem;}
  .team-info{padding:20px 16px;}
  .team-info h4{font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:800;font-size:1.05rem;margin-bottom:4px;letter-spacing:0.04em;}
  .team-info .role{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.7rem;color:var(--orange);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;}
  .team-info p{font-size:0.82rem;color:var(--ink-soft);margin-top:8px;line-height:1.5;}

.cta-strip h2{font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:2.6rem;color:#fff;margin-bottom:12px;}
  .cta-strip p{color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55);margin-bottom:32px;}
  
  .btn-white:hover{background:var(--orange);color:#fff;}

.footer-brand p{font-size:0.84rem;line-height:1.7;margin-top:12px;max-width:250px;}
  .footer-col h4{font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:700;font-size:0.8rem;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.3);margin-bottom:16px;}
  .footer-col ul{list-style:none;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:8px;}
  
  .footer-col a:hover{color:#fff;}
  
  .footer-bottom a{color:rgba(255,255,255,0.3);text-decoration:none;}

  .js-loaded .fade-up.on{opacity:1;transform:none;}

@media(max-width:1024px){
.values-grid,.team-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;}
    .values-section,.team-section,.story-section{padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;}

}
</style>
<div class="page-hero">
  <div class="eyebrow">About</div>
  <h1>Built by People Who<br>Run Athletic Programs</h1>
  <p>ScheduleRama exists because coordinating a season across dozens of schools and leagues was still being done in spreadsheets, email chains, and phone calls.</p>
</div>

<section class="mission-section">
  <div class="mission-text fade-up">
    <div class="eyebrow">Our Mission</div>
    <h2>Give Every Athletic Program a Real Command Center</h2>
    <p>Athletic directors, coaches, and league admins are doing incredible work running programs that matter to their communities. They deserve software that actually fits how they operate — not generic tools bent sideways to handle a sport schedule.</p>
    <p>ScheduleRama is purpose-built for the specific workflows, roles, and communication patterns of high school and amateur athletic programs.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="mission-visual fade-up" style="transition-delay:0.1s;">
    <div class="stat-row">
      <div class="stat-item">
        <div class="stat-num">200+</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Schools Active</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-item">
        <div class="stat-num">40+</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Leagues Running</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-divider"></div>
    <div class="stat-row">
      <div class="stat-item">
        <div class="stat-num">50K+</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Games Scheduled</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-item">
        <div class="stat-num">98%</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Request Resolution</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="values-section">
  <div class="section-head fade-up">
    <div class="eyebrow">What We Believe</div>
    <h2>Principles We Build By</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="values-grid">
    <div class="value-card fade-up">
      <div class="value-ico">🏗️</div>
      <h3>Fit the Workflow, Don't Fight It</h3>
      <p>Every feature is designed around how athletic programs actually operate — not how a generic SaaS company thinks they should. We talk to ADs, coaches, and league admins constantly.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="value-card fade-up" style="transition-delay:0.08s;">
      <div class="value-ico">🔐</div>
      <h3>Roles Matter</h3>
      <p>A coach shouldn't see another school's full schedule. A league admin shouldn't accidentally delete a game. Access control is a core feature, not an afterthought.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="value-card fade-up" style="transition-delay:0.16s;">
      <div class="value-ico">📋</div>
      <h3>Accountability Over Chaos</h3>
      <p>Every request, message, and approval creates a permanent record. "Who confirmed that game?" should have a clear answer — always.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="value-card fade-up" style="transition-delay:0.08s;">
      <div class="value-ico">⚡</div>
      <h3>Speed Without Shortcuts</h3>
      <p>The Group Scheduler pre-populates an entire season in minutes. But it shows you a full preview before committing a single game. Fast and careful aren't opposites.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="value-card fade-up" style="transition-delay:0.16s;">
      <div class="value-ico">🌐</div>
      <h3>Connected Programs</h3>
      <p>Schedules don't exist in isolation. Game Finder connects programs looking for open dates. Requests flow between schools. The network makes everyone's season better.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="value-card fade-up" style="transition-delay:0.24s;">
      <div class="value-ico">📣</div>
      <h3>Less Admin, More Sport</h3>
      <p>Every hour saved on scheduling logistics is an hour someone can spend coaching, developing athletes, or running their program better. That's what we're optimizing for.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="story-section">
  <div class="eyebrow fade-up">Our Story</div>
  <h2 class="fade-up">Where ScheduleRama Came From</h2>
  <p class="fade-up">It started with a frustrating email chain. A league director trying to coordinate 18 schools, 6 sports, and fall and spring seasons — tracking everything in a master spreadsheet that only one person could edit at a time. Conflicts were caught late. Games got double-booked. Coaches were working from outdated PDFs.</p>
  <p class="fade-up">The tools available were either generic calendar apps that didn't understand sports structure, or enterprise systems built for professional leagues that cost more than a school's entire athletics budget.</p>
  <blockquote class="fade-up">"We needed something purpose-built. Something that understands the difference between a request and a confirmation. That knew what a league is, what a level is, what a home-and-away balance means. So we built it."</blockquote>
  <p class="fade-up">ScheduleRama launched with a single league pilot in 2023 and has grown through direct partnerships with athletic directors and league administrators who helped shape every feature. Every workflow in the platform traces back to a real conversation with someone running a real program.</p>
</section>

<section class="team-section">
  <div class="section-head fade-up">
    <div class="eyebrow">The Team</div>
    <h2>Meet the Team — Real experience. Real solutions. Built for you.</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="team-grid">
    <div class="team-card fade-up">
      <div class="team-avatar">⚙️</div>
      <div class="team-info">
        <h4>Tito Soriano</h4>
        <div class="role">Co-Founder</div>
        <p>20+ years working as a Software Developer in Education. With 25+ years of coaching experience, along with serving as Athletic Director, Tito has seen the headaches of managing a season firsthand. Creating an efficient, cost-saving solution to help districts is right in his wheelhouse.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="team-card fade-up" style="transition-delay:0.08s;">
      <div class="team-avatar">📋</div>
      <div class="team-info">
        <h4>Steve Mitzel</h4>
        <div class="role">Co-Founder</div>
        <p>With years of experience as a Director of Operations in education, Steve recognized the need for a solution that creates a supportive environment — one that alleviates the operational headaches that athletic departments so often face when managing a season.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="team-card fade-up" style="transition-delay:0.16s;">
<div class="team-avatar">🤝</div>
      
      <div class="team-info">
        <h4>Brad Eaton</h4>
        <div class="role">Co-Founder</div>
        <p>Obsessive about workflows, Brad ensures every feature starts with a conversation with an actual AD, coach, or league admin before a single line of code is written. His experience as an Athletic Director has been instrumental in shaping Schedulerama into the solution it has become.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="team-card fade-up" style="transition-delay:0.24s;">
      <div class="team-avatar">🎨</div>
      <div class="team-info">
        <h4>Rosie Converse Soriano</h4>
        <div class="role">Director of Marketing</div>
        <p>If you think Schedulerama looks and feels great, you can thank Rosie. As our marketing guru, she brings a sharp, creative eye along with years of experience in athletics and coaching to the team.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="cta-strip">
  <h2>Let's Talk About Your Program</h2>
  <p>We'd love to show you how ScheduleRama fits your specific setup.</p>
  <a href="/contact/" class="btn-white">Book a Demo</a>
</div>
</Base>
